<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B51866DFCDCFC9A093D9241" box="[824,1034,848,871]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fujikuroi">
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B51866DFCDCFC9A0E939241" box="[824,932,848,871]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Fusarium</taxonomicName>
fujikuroi
</taxonomicName>
species complex (
<potCollectionCode id="596C24390B51866DFB3BFC85082B9240" box="[1247,1308,847,870]" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B51866DFB3BFC85082B9240" box="[1247,1308,847,870]" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">FFSC</collectionCode>
</potCollectionCode>
) phylogeny
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32229BC0B51866EFCDCFCBF0FB3931B" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="58" pageId="9" pageNumber="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B877A370B51866DFCDCFCBF08F59538" blockId="9.[824,1474,847,1054]" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">
The eight isolates belonging to the 
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B51866DFB7AFCBE09EB92AD" box="[1182,1244,884,907]" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">
<potCollectionCode id="596C24390B51866DFB7AFCBE09EB92AD" box="[1182,1244,884,907]" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">FFSC</potCollectionCode>
</collectionCode>
were further analysed using a multi-gene phylogeny based on 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFB30FC580826928F" box="[1236,1297,914,937]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">cmdA</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFAF9FC58087B928F" box="[1309,1356,914,937]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">rpb1</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFABCFC5808BF928F" box="[1368,1416,914,937]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">rpb2</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFA77FC58088C928F" box="[1427,1467,914,937]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">tef1</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFC83FC650EB892E0" box="[871,911,943,966]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">tub.</emphasis>
The final alignment included 4 795 characters (
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFA61FC6508F592E0" box="[1413,1474,943,966]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">cmdA</emphasis>
545, 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFC8FFC070EAD92C2" box="[875,922,973,996]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">rpb1</emphasis>
1534, 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFC3BFC07093892C2" box="[991,1039,973,996]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">rpb2</emphasis>
1551, 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFBB0FC07095992C2" box="[1108,1134,973,996]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">tef</emphasis>
677 and 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFB28FC0709DA92C2" box="[1228,1261,973,996]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">tub</emphasis>
488) including align- ment gaps, and encompassed 54 isolates, with two outgroup taxa (
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B51866DFC91FBCD09329538" box="[885,1029,1031,1054]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="oxysporum">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFC91FBCD09329538" box="[885,1029,1031,1054]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B51866DFC91FBCD0EB39538" box="[885,900,1031,1054]" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">F</collectionCodeEnum>
. oxysporum
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
CBS 716.74 and CBS 744.97) (
<tableCitation id="C6BA4F8C0B51866DFA86FBCD08809538" box="[1378,1463,1031,1054]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="4.[111,161,488,510]" captionTargetBox="[111,2088,545,1846]" captionText="Table 2 Fusarium species included in this study." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF472ABF0B5C8660FF8BFE220F1790DB" pageId="9" pageNumber="57" tableUuid="DF472ABF0B5C8660FF8BFE220F1790DB">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF472ABF0B51866DFF95FBA20C7795DC" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">
<paragraph id="8B877A370B51866DFF95FBA20C7795DC" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFF95FBA20D92955C" bold="true" box="[113,165,1128,1146]" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">Fig. 4</emphasis>
Maximum likelihood tree inferred from the combined 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFD65FBA20F9F955C" box="[641,680,1128,1146]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">rpb1</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFD30FBA20FCB955C" box="[724,764,1128,1146]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">rpb2</emphasis>
sequence datasets of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B51866DFEB0FB480F2B95B2" authorityName="Fuckel" authorityYear="1870" box="[340,540,1154,1172]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sambucinum">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFEB0FB480F2B95B2" box="[340,540,1154,1172]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">Fusarium sambucinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex (FSSC) including one Indonesian isolate InaCC F974 (indicated in blue). Bootstrap support values and Bayesian posterior probabilities are given at each node. The tree is rooted to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B51866DFED3FB040CDA95C6" box="[311,493,1230,1248]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="circinatum">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFED3FB040CDA95C6" box="[311,493,1230,1248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">Fusarium circinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(NRRL 25331) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B51866DFD4DFB040D8295DC" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="9" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fujikuroi">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFD4DFB040FCB95C6" box="[681,764,1230,1248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">Fusarium</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B51866DFF95FB220D8295DC" box="[113,181,1256,1274]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="57">fujikuroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(NRRL 13566).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B877A370B52866EFF95FF7A0FB3931B" blockId="10.[113,765,176,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
The analysis was consistently able to distinguish the three biogeographical clades known as the African,American and Asian clades sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA907C60B52866EFEEDFF230F279026" author="O'Donnell K &amp; Cilgenik E &amp; Nirenberg HI" box="[265,528,233,256]" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" pagination="465 - 493" part="90" refId="ref16934" refString="O'Donnell K, Cilgenik E, Nirenberg HI. 1998 a. Molecular systematics and phylogeography of the Gibberella fujikuroi species complex. Mycologia 90: 465 - 493." title="Molecular systematics and phylogeography of the Gibberella fujikuroi species complex" type="journal article" year="1998">
O’Donnell et al. (
<date id="FF865CF70B52866EFE24FF230CCB9026" box="[448,508,233,256]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" value="1998">1998</date>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
. All of the Indonesian isolates clustered within the Asian clade of 
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B52866EFDACFECC0FB0903B" box="[584,647,262,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<potCollectionCode id="596C24390B52866EFDACFECC0FB0903B" box="[584,647,262,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">FFSC</potCollectionCode>
</collectionCode>
except for isolate InaCC 
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B52866EFEE0FEE90C24901C" box="[260,275,291,314]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" type="Herbarium">F</collectionCode>
991, identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFE2DFEE90F55901C" box="[457,610,291,314]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="verticilloides">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFE2DFEE90F55901C" box="[457,610,291,314]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">F. verticilloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and clustered within the African clade (
<figureCitation id="130366B20B52866EFE98FE8A0C889071" box="[380,447,320,343]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[113,145,1953,1971]" captionTargetBox="[164,1437,174,1939]" captionTargetId="graphics@3.[164,1437,174,1880]" captionText="Fig. 2 Maximum likelihood tree inferred from the combined cmdA, tef1, tub, rpb1, and rpb2 sequence datasets of the Fusarium fujikuroi species complex (FFSC) including eight Indonesian isolates (indicated in blue). Bootstrap support values and Bayesian posterior probabilities are given at each node. The tree is rooted to Fusarium nirenbergiae (CBS 744.97) and F. oxysporum (CBS 716.74)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3565712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3565712/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). According to the multi-gene analysis, two isolates (InaCC 
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B52866EFE58FE960CFE9055" box="[444,457,348,371]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B52866EFE58FE960CFE9055" box="[444,457,348,371]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" type="Herbarium">F</collectionCode>
</collectionCodeEnum>
962 and InaCC 
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B52866EFD9AFE960FBC9055" box="[638,651,348,371]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B52866EFD9AFE960FBC9055" box="[638,651,348,371]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" type="Herbarium">F</collectionCode>
</collectionCodeEnum>
992) were identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFF1EFEB30CA590B6" box="[250,402,377,400]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ficidae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="proliferatum">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFF1EFEB30CA590B6" box="[250,402,377,400]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B52866EFF1EFEB30C3E90B6" box="[250,265,377,400]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">F</collectionCodeEnum>
. proliferatum
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while two new phylogenetic species were recognised among the Indonesian isolates. Isolates InaCC 
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B52866EFF24FE790DFA90EC" box="[192,205,435,458]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B52866EFF24FE790DFA90EC" box="[192,205,435,458]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" type="Herbarium">F</collectionCode>
</collectionCodeEnum>
872 and InaCC 
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B52866EFE65FE790CB890EC" box="[385,399,435,458]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B52866EFE65FE790CB890EC" box="[385,399,435,458]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" type="Herbarium">F</collectionCode>
</collectionCodeEnum>
993, from central and 
<collectingRegion id="49FCB4D50B52866EFD6CFE790FCE90EC" box="[648,761,435,458]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">East Java</collectingRegion>
, respectively, clustered in a distinct, highly supported clade (96 bs/0.99 pp) closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFE5DFE260F7B9325" box="[441,588,492,515]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ficidae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mangiferae">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFE5DFE260F7B9325" box="[441,588,492,515]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B52866EFE5DFE260CFF9325" box="[441,456,492,515]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">F</collectionCodeEnum>
. mangiferae
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Isolates InaCC 
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B52866EFF95FDC30D489306" box="[113,127,521,544]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B52866EFF95FDC30D489306" box="[113,127,521,544]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" type="Herbarium">F</collectionCode>
</collectionCodeEnum>
950–152, formed a distinct group (100 bs/1.0 pp), closely related to, but genetically distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFDEFFDEC0F4A931B" baseAuthorityName="Leslie &amp; Summerell" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[523,637,550,573]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ficidae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sacchari">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFDEFFDEC0F4A931B" box="[523,637,550,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B52866EFDEFFDEC0F2D931B" box="[523,538,550,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">F</collectionCodeEnum>
. sacchari
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
